\mathbb{C}
\forall z \ne 0 \in \mathbb{C}, \exists w \in \mathbb{C} \textrm{ such that } zw = 1
z \ne 0
\mathbb{C}
a
b
z = a + bi
z \ne 0
a, b
a^2 + b^2 \ne 0
w = \frac{a - bi}{a^2 + b^2}
z
\mathbb{C}
zw = (a + bi)\frac{a - bi}{a^2 + b^2} = \frac{a^2 + abi - abi - (bi)^2}{a^2 + b^2} = \frac{a^2 + b^2}{a^2 + b^2} = 1
